<subSubSection id="C3186552FF86E30DFF2353FAFA79FFD1" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BBD36D9FF86E30DFF2353FAFA79FFD1" blockId="72.[151,1437,1076,2039]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFF86E30DFF2353FAFEAEFFB5" bold="true" box="[199,334,1184,1210]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a noun in apposition taken from the word “northwest men” in the language of the Chaná, indigenous inhabitants of 
<collectingCountry id="F3157649FF86E30DFDDC539FFD7AFFD0" box="[568,666,1221,1247]" name="Uruguay" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry id="F3157649FF86E30DFCD1539EFC47FFD1" box="[821,935,1220,1246]" name="Argentina" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, in honor of the collectors of the 
<typeStatus id="54B9887BFF86E30DFAFE539FFAAAFFD0" box="[1306,1354,1221,1247]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">type</typeStatus>
series.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3186552FF86E30DFF2353B2FDF8FE9D" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBD36D9FF86E30DFF2353B2FDF8FE9D" blockId="72.[151,1437,1076,2039]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFF86E30DFF2353B2FEA2FE0D" bold="true" box="[199,322,1256,1282]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males (
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFF86E30DFE7953B2FDE4FE0D" box="[413,516,1256,1282]" captionStart="FIGURE 61" captionStartId="76.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@76.[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURE 61. Meriola peras sp. nov. a, female habitus, dorsal view (MACN-Ar 28323); b, same, ventral view; c, same, lateral view; d, prosoma, dorsal view; e, same, ventral view; f, same, lateral view; g, habitus, anterior view. h, male habitus, anterior view (MACN-Ar 28323)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559304" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559304/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 61h</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFF86E30DFDF453B2FDCEFE0D" box="[528,558,1256,1282]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="77.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@77.[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURE 62. Meriola peras sp. nov., male (MACN-Ar 28323). a, habitus, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, same, lateral view; d, prosoma, dorsal view; e, same, ventral view; f, same, lateral view; g, left palp, prolateral view; h, same, ventral view; i, same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559306" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559306/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">62</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFF86E30DFDDF53B2FD84FE0C" box="[571,612,1256,1283]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="78.[151,250,1870,1894]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,181,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-23@78.[173,1413,181,1846]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 63. Meriola peras sp. nov. a, female epigyne, ventral view (MACN-Ar 28323); b, vulva, cleared, ventral view. c, male palp, ventral view, cleared (MACN-Ar 28323). d, female, live specimen (MACN-Ar 30286)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559308" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559308/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">63c</figureCitation>
) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C024D5AFF86E30DFCA053B3FC23FE0D" box="[836,963,1256,1282]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Meriola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcifera">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFF86E30DFCA053B3FC23FE0D" box="[836,963,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. arcifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C024D5AFF86E30DFC1853B3FB99FE0D" box="[1020,1145,1256,1282]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Meriola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decepta">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFF86E30DFC1853B3FB99FE0D" box="[1020,1145,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. decepta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the elongate abdomen and the oval shape of the bulb, but differ from the former by the blunt RTA covered by small bumps, and from the latter by the dark rings on the legs. Females (
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFF86E30DFD7E526AFD0FFE45" box="[666,751,1328,1354]" captionStart="FIGURE 61" captionStartId="76.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-23@76.[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURE 61. Meriola peras sp. nov. a, female habitus, dorsal view (MACN-Ar 28323); b, same, ventral view; c, same, lateral view; d, prosoma, dorsal view; e, same, ventral view; f, same, lateral view; g, habitus, anterior view. h, male habitus, anterior view (MACN-Ar 28323)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559304" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559304/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 61</figureCitation>
a–g, 63a, b, d) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C024D5AFF86E30DFB89526BFB0CFE45" box="[1133,1260,1328,1354]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Meriola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcifera">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFF86E30DFB89526BFB0CFE45" box="[1133,1260,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. arcifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the epigyne lacking a hood and having a wide median field and large, almost contiguous S2, but can be easily recognized by the arc-shaped epigynal lateral ridges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3186552FF86E30FFF2352C6FB6DFEE5" lastPageId="74" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBD36D9FF86E30DFF2352C6FD0AFDF5" blockId="72.[151,1437,1076,2039]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFF86E30DFF2352C6FEB9FEB9" bold="true" box="[199,345,1436,1462]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B976EACBFF86E30DFEBB52C6FE53FEB9" box="[351,435,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54B9887BFF86E30DFE2452C6FDC9FEB8" box="[448,553,1436,1463]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">holotype</typeStatus>
): Carapace length 1.77, width 1.43, narrowed in eye region. Palpal tarsus length 0.45. Sternum length 1.12, width 0.90. Length of tibia/metatarsus: I, 1.35/1.07; II, 1.08/0.90; III, 0.65/0.82; IV, 1.30/1.25. Spines: Leg I, femur p 1ap. IV, femur d 1bas; metatarsus v 0-1-0. Leg cuspules absent. Opisthosoma length 2.63. Color in ethanol: Prosoma reddish-brown, lighter distally. Chelicerae reddish-brown. Legs yellowish-brown, leg I darker. Anterior femora with subbasal and distal dark rings, posterior femora with vague traces of dark rings. All patellae with subdistal, all tibiae with subbasal and distal, all metatarsi with subbasal and distal dark rings. Sternum brown. Opisthosoma grayish-brown, with dark reticulations. Venter grayish. Epigyne (
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFF86E30DFAEA512EFA84FD80" box="[1294,1380,1652,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="78.[151,250,1870,1894]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,181,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-23@78.[173,1413,181,1846]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 63. Meriola peras sp. nov. a, female epigyne, ventral view (MACN-Ar 28323); b, vulva, cleared, ventral view. c, male palp, ventral view, cleared (MACN-Ar 28323). d, female, live specimen (MACN-Ar 30286)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559308" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559308/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 63</figureCitation>
a–b): Arc-shaped epigynal lateral ridges. Copulatory openings in anterior position; copulatory ducts very short, secondary spermathecae large and oval, receptacle of copulatory ducts very small and rounded, behind primary spermathecae. Primary spermathecae rounded and larger than CDR.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBD36D9FF86E30DFF23505EFED7FCF9" blockId="72.[151,1437,1076,2039]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFF86E30DFF23505EFEE1FC11" box="[199,257,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54B9887BFF86E30DFEF4505EFE98FC11" box="[272,376,1796,1822]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">paratype</typeStatus>
): Carapace length 1.87, width 1.40, narrowed in eye region. Palpal tarsus length 0.53. Sternum length 1.13, width 0.94. Length of tibia/metatarsus: I, 1.58/1.33; II, 1.03/0.93; III, 0.72/0.83; IV, 1.13/1.38. Spines: Leg I, femur p 1ap. II, femur p 1ap. III, metatarsus v 0-1-0. IV, femur d 1bas; metatarsus v 0-1-0. Leg cuspules (left or right): Leg I, tibia 5 or 7, metatarsus 15, tarsus 6. II, tibia 5 or 4, metatarsus 8 or 6. Opisthosoma length 2.34. Opisthosoma with dorsal oval, slightly sclerotized area, limited to posterior half of abdomen. Coloration as in female. Palp (
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFF86E30DFEFF50E2FE90FCDD" box="[283,368,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="77.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@77.[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURE 62. Meriola peras sp. nov., male (MACN-Ar 28323). a, habitus, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, same, lateral view; d, prosoma, dorsal view; e, same, ventral view; f, same, lateral view; g, left palp, prolateral view; h, same, ventral view; i, same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559306" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559306/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 62</figureCitation>
g–i, 63c): Tibia short. RTA short, blunt, covered by small bumps. Embolus short, slightly curved to retrolateral.
</paragraph>
